{{Quote|I was a Star Trek fan first. But I've got to be honest, when Star Wars came out, I took down all Star Trek posters in my bedroom and plastered my wall with Star Wars. It took over our territory.|Dan Madsen|<ref name="HowSWConquered">{{BookCite|author=Taylor, Chris|title=How Star Wars Conquered the Universe: The Past, Present, and Future of a Multibillion Dollar Franchise|publisher=Basic Books|date=2014-09-30|isbn=9781784970475|link=https://archive.org/details/howstarwarsconqu0000tayl_r2z1/page/n515/mode/2up}}</ref>}}
'''Dan Madsen''' is a former president of the Official Star Wars Fan Club and the founder and former publisher of the ''Star Wars Insider'' magazine. A journalistic writer, he contributed many of the interviews and pieces to the [[Star Wars Insider|''Lucasfilm Fan Club Magazine'']] as well as writing the "Making Of" book for ''The Young Indiana Jones Chronicles'' TV series. He made a cameo appearance in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] as a [[kaadu]] handler, dubbed [[Dams Denna/Legends|Dams Denna]] in [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]]. He is the original producer and event organizer of the very first [[Celebration (1999)|''Star Wars'' Celebration]] in Denver, Colorado, in 1999.

He attended the [[Starlog Salutes Star Wars|Star Wars 10th anniversary convention]], where he took the only known photograph of [[George Lucas]] meeting [[Wikipedia:Gene Roddenberry|Gene Roddenberry]].<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.trekcore.com/specials/tenforward/article5|text=Dan Madsen: Star Trek's Fan Communicator|archivedate=20180101232711}}</ref>

